# Description

distributing a tarball with O(100) files is a bit overwhelming. I think it would be better to define a patch set, which could just be 

```
[
  {
    "metadata": {
        "sbottom_mass": 100,
        "neutralino_mass": 300
    },
    "patch": [
        {"op": "replace"},
        {"op": "replace"}
    ]
  },
  {
    "metadata": {
        "sbottom_mass": 200,
        "neutralino_mass": 400
    },
    "patch": [
        {"op": "replace"},
        {"op": "replace"}
    ]
  }
]
```

to get a specific patch one could do:
```
cat patchset.json|ca|jq '.[]|select(
.metadata.sbottom_mass == 100 and \
.metadata.neutralino_mass == 300
).patch'
```
This way for example the sbottom hepdata tarball would only be 6 files

* RegionA/BkgOnly.json
* RegionA/SignalPatchSet.json
* RegionB/BkgOnly.json
* RegionB/SignalPatchSet.json
* RegionC/BkgOnly.json
* RegionC/SignalPatchSet.json

